-- Lawyer confirms surrender of Bulgarian Corpbank's main shareholder
-- By Tsvetelia Tsolova
-- Tue Sep 16, 2014 10:05AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, Sept 16 (Reuters) - Tsvetan Vassilev, the majority owner of Bulgaria's troubled Corporate Commercial Bank (Corpbank) <6C9.BB>, has surrendered to Serbian police on an international arrest warrant for embezzlement, his lawyer said on Tuesday.

A senior source at Serbia's interior ministry had told Reuters earlier that Vassilev has handed himself in to Serbian authorities. [ID:nL6N0RH2QI]